                </div> -->
                <img src=" images/fielddeployment/hanging.png " alt="hanging ">
                </br>
                </br>
                <img src="images/fielddeployment/surface.png " alt="surface ">
              </li>
              <br>
              <li>Once sensor is plugged in make sure the LED is on solid (except flicker-flashes every one-minute indicating data logging) </li>
              <li>If LED is not solid, ensure the SD is properly inserted and try unplugging the sensor from the power source (battery or wall) and reconnecting. </li>
              <li>Ensure all cords are out of the way </li>
              <li>Fill out “real-time log sheet"</li>
            </ol>
            <br>

            <h4>Real-Time Sensors Outside of Homes</h4>
            <ol>
              <li>Select a location for the monitor based on the list of preferences below:
                <ul>
                  <li>On same level as residence (e.g. balcony)</li>
                  <li>On roof</li>
                  <li>On ground floor (e.g. fence, guard station, etc.) • This is preferable if the residence is significantly closer to the ground floor than to the roof.</li>
                  <li>Nearby accessible location (e.g. university building)</li>
                  <li>Use a close by monitor outside a neighboring home</li>
                </ul>
              </li>
              <li>Ensure the monitor is secured using zip ties and avoid situations where monitors could fall multiple stories if they become detached.</li>
              <li>Use wall power if readily available otherwise plug in battery.</li>
              </br>
              <img src="images/fielddeployment/outdoor.png " alt="outdoor">
            </ol>
            </br>

            <h4>Factors to consider when selecting deployment location: </h4>
            <ol>
              <li>Security and safety if instrument were to become detached (do not hang out window)</li>
              <li>Ease of access to replace battery every 2-3 days</li>
              <li>Location of the time integrated package: locate together if possible (if time integrated package can be located in locations 1-3)</li>
              <li>Possible theft or tampering with devices if they are easily accessible to the public</li>
            </ol>

            <h4>Air purifiers in homes:</h4>
            <ol>
              <li>Ensure windows are closed in participant’s bedroom and remind participant to keep them closed.</li>
              <li>Set up air purifier in participant’s bedroom.</li>
              <li>Plug in and turn to setting 3.</li>
            </ol>

            <h4>Return visits to Home:</h4>
            <ol>
              <li>Replace real-time battery every 3 days or every time you visit the home for other purposes </li>
              <li>Download data 2x per week to ensure it is logging </li>
              <li>Fill out “real-time log sheet”</li>
              <li>Make sure to recharge discharged batteries as soon as returning to the lab. Unplug once fully charged as indicated by LED. The batteries have 4 lights indicating charge level, when the battery is charged all 4 lights will be on.</li>
            </ol>

